    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-31T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-31T03:00:00-05:00" n="718"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/584: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-31T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 31, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 31—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 30, 11 a.m. I have just seen Lampson, to whom I gave the information
                    reported in my March 30, 1 p.m. He stated he was leaving on April 2 for Peiping,
                    expecting to be away approximately 10 days to 2 weeks. I assume, therefore, that
                    C. T. Wang has not gone beyond the point reported in my March 30, 11 a.m. Dr.
                    Wang apparently wishes to see if we are disposed to go further than the British
                    before he resumes negotiations with them here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
